key_trends: Rise of serverless and edge computing

competitive_positioning.competitive_moat: Open-source ecosystem, strong community, and ease of use create a significant barrier to entry.
competitive_positioning.differentiation: Open-source alternative to Firebase with a focus on Postgres and a comprehensive suite of tools.
competitive_advantages: Postgres-centric approach appeals to many developers
competitive_vulnerabilities: Reliance on Postgres may limit appeal to some developers
Competition from established players like Firebase and AWS

growth_indicators: Rapid user adoption and community growth
Increasing number of integrations and partnerships
growth_bottlenecks: Scaling infrastructure to meet growing demand

key_risks: Maintaining developer trust and community engagement

next_steps: Continue to invest in community building and open-source contributions
expansion_opportunities: Offer managed services for other databases
Develop new features and integrations to attract more developers
